#build into binary
target FreeBSD:
    GOOS=freebsd GOARCH=amd64 go build -o webmanager

✅ Step 1: Pindahkan binary ke tempat permanen
Misal taruh di /usr/local/bin:
$ sudo cp ./webmanager /usr/local/bin/
$ sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/webmanager

✅ Step 2: Buat file rc.d script
Buat file baru:
$ sudo ee /usr/local/etc/rc.d/webmanager
Isi dengan:
#!/bin/sh

# PROVIDE: webmanager
# REQUIRE: LOGIN
# KEYWORD: shutdown

. /etc/rc.subr

name="webmanager"
rcvar=webmanager_enable

command="/usr/local/bin/webmanager"
pidfile="/var/run/${name}.pid"
command_args="> /var/log/${name}.log 2>&1 & echo \$! > $pidfile"

start_cmd="${name}_start"
stop_cmd="${name}_stop"

webmanager_start() {
    echo "Starting ${name}..."
    eval "${command} ${command_args}"
}

webmanager_stop() {
    echo "Stopping ${name}..."
    kill `cat $pidfile` && rm -f $pidfile
}

load_rc_config $name
run_rc_command "$1"
Simpan dan keluar.

✅ Step 3: Buat log file dan PID folder
$ sudo touch /var/log/webmanager.log
$ sudo mkdir -p /var/run

✅ Step 4: Aktifkan di rc.conf
$ sudo sysrc webmanager_enable=YES

✅ Step 5: Coba jalankan
$ sudo service webmanager start
Cek:
$ ps aux | grep webmanager
$tail -f /var/log/webmanager.log

Stop service:
$ sudo service webmanager stop

prerequisites:
- sudo
- bastille 0.14
- edit /usr/local/etc/sudoers, insert this line below
<your username> ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD:/usr/local/bin/bastille

how to use:
- upload binary to your home in FreeBSD machine. then edit .env:
    - default app port is 8000
    - Whitelist is used for ignoring request from other IP, set ip whitelist using your client machine ip and if you have multiple IP, separate with commas without space, for example IP_WHITELIST=1.1.1.1,2.2.2.2 etc. 